fields.name: Gal Gallop
fields.details: Don't have to be fast or able to run 20 miles for this one. Only requirement is to not be a guy! It's all about having fun in a supportive, non-competitive trail environment. Goes at the pace of the slowest runner -- beginner-friendly. Runs on the Kansas River "Sandrat" trails. (Bring a light in the winter seasons).
fields.location: Meet in the trailhead parking lot just off 8th & Oak in north Lawrence.

fields.name: Humday Run
fields.details: Run about 5.5 to 12 miles on technical trail. Sometimes go out for dinner after. Don't forget to bring a headlamp and water.
fields.location: Meet at the Corps of Engineers parking lot, Clinton Lake north shore trail head

fields.name: Beginners Run
fields.details: An easy-paced run of five miles or less on the Kansas River "Sandrat" trails. Bring a water bottle and a light. Good for veteran trail runners too, who just want to get some nice easy miles in.
fields.location: Meet in the trailhead parking lot just off 8th & Oak in north Lawrence.

fields.name: Saturday Long Run
fields.details: Normally do about 10 -30 miles on technical trail, though there are plenty of turn-arounds if you want to go shorter. Field trips to Perry Lake for long runs there are planned for later this summer.
fields.location: Meet at the Corps of Engineers parking lot, Clinton Lake north shore trail head

fields.title: Hawk50 - marathon
fields.discounts: Dues-paying Trail Hawks subtract $5 from entry fee.
fields.description: Trail run with rocky, rooty sections, and smooth flat sections. Scenic lake views. Beautiful shady woods. Two traverses of scenic Sanders' Mound.

fields.title: Sanders Saunter
fields.description: Trail run with rocky, rooty sections, and smooth flat sections. Scenic lake views. Beautiful shady woods. With two passings over Sanders Mound.
fields.packet_pickup: Pre-Race packet pickup is at Gary Gribbles in Lawrence on Saturday, Nov. 21 2009 from 1-3 pm.
fields.reg_description: Race Day, Corps of Engineering Parking lot. Mail-in registration available. Check-in and race day registration begin at 8:00 a.m.

fields.title: Shoreline Shuffle
fields.location:
Shelter 4, Campground 1, Clinton Lake State Park
798 N 1415 Rd., Lawrence, KS 66049
fields.description: Trail run with rocky, rooty sections, and smooth flat sections. Scenic lake views. Beautiful shady woods. Possible sightings of the Clinton Lake sea serpent 'Clintie'.
fields.reg_description: Mail-in $8/$4 for dues-paying Trail Hawks. Race day $10/$5 for dues- paying Trail Hawks. Race entry DOES NOT include $4.20 per vehicle Kansas State Park entry fee for vehicles without an annual entry permit sticker.
